index 8cb14ddb65..9ccae19573 100644
--- a/docs/src/config/ini-config.adoc
+++ b/docs/src/config/ini-config.adoc
@@ -704,6 +704,12 @@ For more information on the motion controller see the <<sec:motion,Motion>> sect
   This parameter affects the polling interval when waiting for motion to complete, when executing a pause instruction, and when accepting a command from a user interface.
   There is usually no need to change this number.
   Defaults to 0.100 if omitted.
+* `STOP_PRESERVE_PROGRAM = TRUE` -
+  When true (the default), the dedicated Stop command preserves an active AUTO
+  program and its queued motion so it can be continued with Run or Resume.
+  Motion decelerates to a safe boundary before spindle and coolant outputs are
+  stopped.  When false, or outside active AUTO execution, Stop performs the
+  same full abort as the Abort command.
 
